What is API? Name list of API that you have used so far.
A. API is Application Programmimg Interface which is an interface that faciliates the interaction among application .
In the context of Java, API is a collection of prewritten packages, classes, and interfaces with their respective methods,
 fields and constructors. Similar to a user interface, which facilitates interaction between humans and computers,
 an API serves as a software program interface facilitating interaction.
 The API that we have used java.util,java.lang, java.io,java.math,java.sql

Does java support multiple inheritance, explain why or why not?
A. No java does not support multiple inheritance. Probably the language desinger have desinged this way to avoid  ambiguity.
Although Java class doesn't achieve multiple inheritance through class but it can somehow achieve this by implementing more than one
ifterfaces.

What is method overloading and when it happens?
A. Method Overloading is a feature that allow more than one  methods to  have same name but differnt number of arguments.

Explain exceptions in java and how to handle it.
Exceptions are events that occur during the execution of programs that disrupt the normal
flow of instructions (e.g. divide by zero, array access out of bound, etc.). In Java, an
exception is an object that wraps an error event that occurred within a method and contains
 Information about the error including its type.

What is static keyword in java? How it has been used in variables and methods ?
The static keyword is used in java mainly for memory management. It is used with variables, methods,
blocks and nested class. It is a keyword that are used for share the same variable or method of a given class.
This is used for a constant variable or a method that is the same for every instance of a class

